# Bundle Test Conventions

## General

- `declare(strict_types=1)` in test files too
- Structure: `tests/Unit/`, `tests/Integration/`, `tests/Functional/`
- Use `nyholm/symfony-bundle-test` with `TestKernel` for integration tests

## Minimum Required Tests

- Bundle boots without error
- All services are correctly registered and wired
- Configuration validation (required keys, invalid values)

## Integration Test Template

```php
use Nyholm\BundleTest\TestKernel;
use Symfony\Bundle\FrameworkBundle\Test\KernelTestCase;

protected static function getKernelClass(): string
{
    return TestKernel::class;
}

protected static function createKernel(array $options = []): KernelInterface
{
    $kernel = parent::createKernel($options);
    $kernel->addTestBundle(AcmeBlogBundle::class);
    $kernel->addTestConfig(function ($container) {
        $container->loadFromExtension('acme_blog', ['api_key' => 'test']);
    });
    $kernel->handleOptions($options);
    return $kernel;
}
```

## Live Components

Test with `InteractsWithLiveComponents` trait in `KernelTestCase`:

```php
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Test\InteractsWithLiveComponents;

$component = $this->createLiveComponent(name: SearchLive::class, data: ['query' => 'test']);
$component->call('loadMore');
self::assertSame(2, $component->component()->page);
```

## Twig Components

Test rendering via Twig render assertions or by checking rendered HTML output.

## After Every Change

Run `make test` then `make infection` to verify coverage and mutation score.
